    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">  The fun part is to watch smeagol pound on things, and peoples reaction when you play smeagol as your only companion. You can easily play this deck as a Culture Shock deck by removeing the two Power According to His Stature, and adding one each of Don&#39;t Look at Them and One Good Turn Deserves Another.<br />
 <br />
Free Peoples <br />
<br />
  Bid nothing to go first. Use your One Good turn Deserves Another and Still Far Ahead to control the site path. The Where Shall We Gos are there to filter your hand. I usually hold a copy or two of Clever Hobbits in my hand for the occassional large minion (Sauron, Balrog) or Swarm (Moria)discard the Don&#39;t Look at Them first. The Power According to His Stature is good against swarm decks as well.<br />
<br />
Shadow<br />
<br />
  This is a pretty basic swarm deck. Use the Spurred to Battles, Foraging Orc and Scurrying Goblins to add twilight to the pool. Then use the Skulking Goblins to make sites into underground (especially Fangorn Glade), play Denizen of Khazad-Dum, Denizen of Moria, and Frenzied orc to capitalize on the underground sites. Exert to play Champion Orcs.<br />
<br />
